    prism.Prism.buildModel(ModulesFile)
    Load a PRISM model, build it, store for later use and return. Reachability and model construction are done symbolically, i.e. using (MT)BDDs. It is assumed that all constants in the PRISM model file have been defined by now.

    prism.Prism.doSteadyState(Model)
    Load (built) model and compute steady-state probabilities (DTMCs/CTMCs only). Output probability distribution to log.
    prism.Prism.doSteadyState(Model, int, File)
    Load (built) model and compute steady-state probabilities (DTMCs/CTMCs only). Output probability distribution to a file (or, if file is null, to log). The exportType should be EXPORT_PLAIN or EXPORT_MATLAB.
    prism.Prism.doTransient(Model, double)
    Load (built) model and compute transient probabilities (DTMCs/CTMCs only). Output probability distribution to log.
    prism.Prism.doTransient(Model, double, int, File, File)
    Load (built) model and compute transient probabilities (DTMCs/CTMCs only). Output probability distribution to a file (or, if file is null, to log). The exportType should be EXPORT_PLAIN or EXPORT_MATLAB. Optionally (if non-null), read in the initial probability distribution from a file.
    prism.Prism.exportBSCCsToFile(Model, int, File)
    Load a (built) model and export its bottom strongly connected components (BSCCs) to a file
    prism.Prism.exportLabelsToFile(Model, ModulesFile, PropertiesFile, int, File)
    Load a (built) model and export the states satisfying labels from it and a properties file to a file The PropertiesFile should correspond to the model.
